  "local_port": 46976,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "If you're looking to minimize or eliminate US election news from your Quora feed, you can adjust your settings and preferences to better tailor the content you see. Below are several steps you can take to achieve this:\n\n### 1. **Unfollow Relevant Topics**\n\nQuora organizes content around topics that users follow. To reduce election-related content, you can unfollow topics that are closely associated with US elections.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Go to Your Profile:**\n   - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select \"Settings\" or \"Profile\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n2. **Manage Followed Topics:**\n   - Navigate to the \"Following\" section.\n   - Browse through the list of topics you follow.\n   - Look for topics related to US elections, such as:\n     - **US Elections**\n     - **Politics**\n     - **Democracy**\n     - **Political Campaigns**\n     - **Voting**\n   - Click the \"Following\" button next to these topics to unfollow them.\n\n### 2. **Adjust Your Following Preferences**\n\nIn addition to unfollowing specific topics, you can refine the types of content you see by adjusting your overall topic preferences.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Access Settings:**\n   - Click on your profile picture and go to \"Settings.\"\n\n2. **Navigate to Feed Preferences:**\n   - Look for sections like \"Content Preferences\" or \"Feed Preferences.\"\n\n3. **Customize Your Feed:**\n   - Deselect categories related to politics and elections.\n   - Prioritize topics you are more interested in to naturally push unrelated content higher in your feed.\n\n### 3. **Use the \"Don't Show\" Feature**\n\nQuora allows users to hide specific types of content or individual answers that they\u2019re not interested in.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Identify Unwanted Content:**\n   - When you see a US election-related question or answer, look for the three-dot menu (`\u22ee`) next to it.\n\n2. **Hide the Content:**\n   - Click on the three dots.\n   - Select options like \"Hide question,\" \"Hide answer,\" or \"Report\" if the content is inappropriate.\n\n3. **Provide Feedback:**\n   - When hiding content, you might be prompted to provide a reason. Choose relevant options to help Quora understand your preferences better.\n\n### 4. **Block Specific Users or Sources**\n\nIf certain users frequently post US election content, you can block them to prevent their content from appearing in your feed.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit the User\u2019s Profile:**\n   - Click on the user\u2019s name or profile picture.\n\n2. **Access Blocking Options:**\n   - Click on the three-dot menu (`\u22ee`) on their profile.\n\n3. **Block the User:**\n   - Select \"Block\" from the dropdown options.\n   - Confirm your choice when prompted.\n\n### 5. **Utilize Search Filters**\n\nWhen searching for content or topics on Quora, use filters to exclude election-related keywords.\n\n**Example:**\n- Instead of searching for \"Elections,\" try using terms like \"Current Events\" or specific interests that don\u2019t relate to politics.\n\n### 6. **Provide Feedback to Quora**\n\nQuora continuously updates its platform based on user feedback. Letting them know your preferences can help improve your experience.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Go to Help Center:**\n   - Scroll to the bottom of any Quora page and click on \"Help\" or \"Help Center.\"\n\n2. **Submit Feedback:**\n   - Look for an option to provide feedback or report an issue.\n   - Clearly state that you wish to minimize or remove US election-related content from your feed.\n\n### 7. **Regularly Review Your Settings**\n\nQuora periodically updates its features and settings. Make it a habit to review your preferences to ensure they align with your current interests.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Check Notifications:**\n   - Sometimes, Quora may suggest new topics or content based on your activity. Adjust your interactions accordingly.\n\n2. **Update Followed Topics:**\n   - Periodically revisit your followed topics and make adjustments as needed.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Be Selective in Interactions:** Quora\u2019s algorithm tends to show more of what you interact with. If you avoid upvoting, commenting, or clicking on US election content, it may reduce similar content in your feed over time.\n\n- **Explore New Topics:** Engage with a variety of other topics you\u2019re interested in. This diversification can help balance your feed and push less desired content further down.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to significantly reduce the presence of US election news in your Quora feed, allowing you to focus on the content that matters most to you.\n\nIf you encounter any challenges or if Quora updates its interface, referring to Quora's [Help Center](https://help.quora.com/) for the latest guidance is recommended.",
